verbatimLocality: Fossil Creek Community Park, Fort Collins, CO, US
occurrenceRemarks: Plant about three feet tall with alternating leaves. Smooth stem. Thin fuzzy hairs on leaves. One main vein on leaves with straight smaller veins that go out to the leaves edge. Leaf edges are smooth. White tap root. Flowers are five petaled, grow in clumps, have dark pink centers and white tips. Pollinated by western honey bees. Creates milky sap that is a skin irritant. Smooth hairless stem.
